article.headline: Ill-Chicago 72, Wis-Milwaukee 59
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Othyus Jeffers scored 15 points and Jovan Stefanov added 13 as Illinois-Chicago beat Wisconsin-Milwaukee 72-59 Wednesday night. Jeffers had six rebounds and five assists for the Flames (12-17, 6-9 Horizon League), who led 42-27 at the half. Stefanov added seven rebounds and four assists. Wisconsin-Milwaukee's Roman Gentry led all scorers with 17 points and nine rebounds on 7-of-11 shooting. Marcus Skinner and Avery Smith both added nine for the Panthers (8-21, 5-10). Scott VanderMeer added 12 points for the Flames, including five rebounds. Josh Mayo chipped in 11 points and eight rebounds for the team, which scored 15 points off turnovers compared with just eight for the Panthers. It was the second straight victory for the Flames, who edged one step closer to securing a home opening game in next week's Horizon League Tournament.
